<Layout
  title="Gopher Control Cost Guide 2026 | How Much Does It Actually Cost?"
  description="Honest breakdown of what every gopher control method costs — from $15 traps to $500 pro jobs. Mark the Bagger compares all 13 methods by price, reusability, and value."
  schemas={[faqSchema]}
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> › Gopher Control Costs
  </nav>

  <header>
    <h1>How Much Does Gopher Control Cost?</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Honest numbers for every method — from a $0 garden hose trick to $500 pro jobs.</p>
    <p class="dateline">Updated March 2026</p>
  </header>

  <main>

    <section class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #10b981;">
      <p style="margin: 0; color: #374151; font-size: 0.95rem;">Most gopher problems are solved with a $15 pair of Victor traps and an hour of work. But not every situation calls for the same approach — and knowing what things actually cost before you start saves you from blowing money on methods that won't work for your yard. Here's every method I cover on this site, broken down by real cost.</p>
    </section>

    <nav class="card" aria-label="Table of contents" style="border-left: 4px solid #059669; padding: 1rem 1.5rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #6b7280; margin: 0 0 0.65rem;">In This Guide</p>
      <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.9; font-size: 0.9rem;">
        <li><a href="#full-comparison">Full Cost Comparison Table</a></li>
        <li><a href="#under-30">Under $30 — Cheap &amp; Effective</a></li>
        <li><a href="#30-to-150">$30–$150 — Mid-Range Options</a></li>
        <li><a href="#150-plus">$150+ — Big Property &amp; Pro-Level</a></li>
        <li><a href="#best-value">Mark's Best Value Picks</a></li>
        <li><a href="#faq">Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- Full Comparison Table -->
    <section class="card">
      <h2 id="full-comparison">Full Cost Comparison — All 13 Methods</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: #6b7280; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Sorted cheapest to most expensive. "Ongoing" means you'll spend money repeatedly. "One-time" means buy it once and you're done.</p>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="cost-table">
          <thead>
